        "### Exercise 2 â€” Decision Tree Interpretation\n",
        "1. Compute Gini for both features at the root (manual verification).\n",
        "2. Use the tree to estimate probabilities for a sample with petal length=5 cm and petal width=1.5 cm.\n",
        "3. Trace path and verify prediction with `predict`."
      ]

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 3,
      "id": "69b3fb44",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "69b3fb44",
        "outputId": "16806513-ff89-4107-d8a9-990e2319649e"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Root Gini (all samples): 0.6666666666666667\n",
            "Best split found (approx):\n",
            "petal length threshold 1.9 gini after split 0.3333333333333333\n",
            "petal width threshold 0.6 gini after split 0.3333333333333333\n",
            "\n",
            "Predicted class probabilities for petal length=5, petal width=1.5:\n",
            "setosa: 0.0000\n",
            "versicolor: 0.9074\n",
            "virginica: 0.0926\n",
            "\n",
            "Leaf id for the sample: [3]\n",
            "Decision path:\n",
            "node 0: (feature petal length (cm) <= 2.4500)\n",
            "node 2: (feature petal width (cm) <= 1.7500)\n",
            "node 3: leaf\n",
            "\n",
            "Predicted class (predict): versicolor\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "from collections import Counter\n",
        "\n",
        "def gini_of_labels(labels):\n",
        "    counts = np.array(list(Counter(labels).values()), dtype=float)\n",
        "    probs = counts / counts.sum()\n",
        "    return 1.0 - np.sum(probs**2)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Root gini (entire dataset)\n",
        "root_gini = gini_of_labels(y)\n",
        "print('Root Gini (all samples):', root_gini)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Evaluate splitting by a threshold on petal length and petal width to check which feature is chosen\n",
        "thresholds = {\n",
        "    'petal length': np.unique(X[:,0]),\n",
        "    'petal width': np.unique(X[:,1])\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "def gini_for_split(feature_col, thresh):\n",
        "    left_idx = feature_col <= thresh\n",
        "    right_idx = ~left_idx\n",
        "    n = len(feature_col)\n",
        "    g_left = gini_of_labels(y[left_idx])\n",
        "    g_right = gini_of_labels(y[right_idx])\n",
        "    return (left_idx.sum()/n)*g_left + (right_idx.sum()/n)*g_right\n",
        "\n",
        "# compute best split (Gini) for each feature\n",
        "best = {}\n",
        "for i, name in enumerate(['petal length','petal width']):\n",
        "    col = X[:, i]\n",
        "    best_score = 1.0\n",
        "    best_thresh = None\n",
        "    for t in np.unique(col):\n",
        "        score = gini_for_split(col, t)\n",
        "        if score < best_score:\n",
        "            best_score = score\n",
        "            best_thresh = t\n",
        "    best[name] = (best_thresh, best_score)\n",
        "\n",
        "print('Best split found (approx):')\n",
        "for k,v in best.items():\n",
        "    print(k, 'threshold', v[0], 'gini after split', v[1])\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2) predict proba for the sample [5, 1.5]\n",
        "sample = np.array([[5.0, 1.5]])\n",
        "proba = tree_clf.predict_proba(sample)\n",
        "print('\\nPredicted class probabilities for petal length=5, petal width=1.5:')\n",
        "for cname, p in zip(class_names, proba[0]):\n",
        "    print(f'{cname}: {p:.4f}')\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3) trace the path using decision_path and node indicators\n",
        "node_indicator = tree_clf.decision_path(sample)\n",
        "leaf_id = tree_clf.apply(sample)\n",
        "print('\\nLeaf id for the sample:', leaf_id)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Show the rules (walk the tree)\n",
        "feature = tree_clf.tree_.feature\n",
        "threshold = tree_clf.tree_.threshold\n",
        "node_index = node_indicator.indices[node_indicator.indptr[0]:node_indicator.indptr[1]]\n",
        "print('Decision path:')\n",
        "for node_id in node_index:\n",
        "    if feature[node_id] != -2:\n",
        "        print(f\"node {node_id}: (feature {feature_names[feature[node_id]]} <= {threshold[node_id]:.4f})\")\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        print(f\"node {node_id}: leaf\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4) verify predict\n",
        "pred = tree_clf.predict(sample)\n",
        "print('\\nPredicted class (predict):', iris.target_names[pred][0])"
      ]

      "source": [
        "from sklearn.model_selection import KFold\n",
        "\n",
        "def kfoldCrossValidation(X, y, M, k=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42):\n",
        "    kfold = KFold(n_splits=k, shuffle=shuffle, random_state=random_state)\n",
        "    scores = []\n",
        "    for train_index, test_index in kfold.split(X):\n",
        "        X_train, X_test = X[train_index], X[test_index]\n",
        "        y_train, y_test = y[train_index], y[test_index]\n",
        "        M.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "        y_pred = M.predict(X_test)\n",
        "        scores.append(accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))\n",
        "    return np.array(scores)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Test k values\n",
        "for k in [2, 3, 5, 10]:\n",
        "    scores = kfoldCrossValidation(X, y, DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=2, random_state=42), k=k)\n",
        "    print(f'k={k}: scores={scores}, avg={scores.mean():.4f}')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Build another decision tree using all features without max_depth constraint and compare\n",
        "X_all = iris.data\n",
        "clf_unconstrained = DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42)\n",
        "clf_unconstrained_scores = kfoldCrossValidation(X_all, y, clf_unconstrained, k=5)\n",
        "clf_constrained_scores = kfoldCrossValidation(X_all[:, 2:], y, DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=2, random_state=42), k=5)\n",
        "print('\\nUsing all features (unconstrained tree) 5-fold avg:', clf_unconstrained_scores.mean())\n",
        "print('Using petal features (max_depth=2) 5-fold avg:', clf_constrained_scores.mean())\n",
        "\n",
        "print('\\nIntuition: larger k gives less biased estimate but higher variance; unconstrained tree tends to overfit and may have higher CV variance.')"
      ]
    },

        "from sklearn.metrics import classification_report\n",
        "\n",
        "# Iris â€” train/test split\n",
        "X_iris = iris.data\n",
        "y_iris = iris.target\n",
        "Xtr, Xte, ytr, yte = train_test_split(X_iris, y_iris, test_size=0.3, random_state=42, stratify=y_iris)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Baseline Logistic Regression\n",
        "lr = LogisticRegression(max_iter=500, solver='lbfgs', multi_class='auto', random_state=42)\n",
        "lr.fit(Xtr, ytr)\n",
        "y_pred = lr.predict(Xte)\n",
        "print('Logistic Regression (no PCA) â€” classification report:')\n",
        "print(classification_report(yte, y_pred, target_names=iris.target_names))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Apply PCA (keep 2 components) and re-train\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "Xtr_s = scaler.fit_transform(Xtr)\n",
        "Xte_s = scaler.transform(Xte)\n",
        "\n",
        "pca = PCA(n_components=2)\n",
        "Xtr_pca = pca.fit_transform(Xtr_s)\n",
        "Xte_pca = pca.transform(Xte_s)\n",
        "\n",
        "lr_pca = LogisticRegression(max_iter=500, random_state=42)\n",
        "lr_pca.fit(Xtr_pca, ytr)\n",
        "y_pred_pca = lr_pca.predict(Xte_pca)\n",
        "print('\\nLogistic Regression (PCA 2 components) â€” classification report:')\n",
        "print(classification_report(yte, y_pred_pca, target_names=iris.target_names))\n",
        "\n",
        "print('\\nExplained variance ratio (PCA 2 components):', pca.explained_variance_ratio_)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Compare with a simple Decision Tree baseline (unconstrained)\n",
        "dt_baseline = DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42)\n",
        "dt_baseline.fit(Xtr, ytr)\n",
        "y_pred_dt = dt_baseline.predict(Xte)\n",
        "print('\\nDecision Tree (no constraint) â€” classification report:')\n",
        "print(classification_report(yte, y_pred_dt, target_names=iris.target_names))"
      ]
    },
